long_desc.thetext:
responsible for this behaviour are checks in InternalCompositeTable:
fireRequestRowChangeEvent() and fireRowDepartEvent() both have 

if (rows.size() < 1 || (currentRow < 1)) {
            return true;
        }

currentRow is 0 when you edit row 0 and the methods therefore skips firering the events. I changed both to 

if (rows.size() < 1 || (currentRow < 1 && topRow != 0)) {
        return;
}

and row 0 now fires correctly. I'm not quite sure why to skip fireing if currentRow < 1 so I'm not sure about other unwanted effects. I'll further investigate the whole event behaviour.

The xml truncation is a bug in 2.0.1 and has been fixed in 2.1.

The key problem of this is that,

In method	org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler.characters(char[], int start, int length) , which is used to rechieve value of an xml element,
the first argument, that is, char[], which is a cache of xml input stream, passed by the Xerces parser would always be of 2048 bytes in length. If a value of an xml element exceeds 2048 bytes, or only parts of its value being cached on the rear of the char array, then the method characters() will be called multiple times so that the whole value could be achieved.

So, to fix the problem in 2.0.1, what you need to do is just cache the value read from "characters()" method until the whole value of element is read. You can reference to latest XML driver for details. The class related to this problem is SaxParser.java.

Please notice that the whole XML driver has been moved to DtP project.To save your time I give some pseduo code:

1. In class member data declaration, add following:

private String currentCacheValue = "";

2. Override method characters() as follows:
  public void characters( char ch[], int start, int length )
  {
	for ( int i = 0; i < length; i++ )
	{
        	this.currentCacheValue = this.currentCacheValue + ch[start + i];
	}	
  }
3. Change method endElement as follows:

In method endElement( String uri, String localName, String qName )
			throws SAXException
{
	//Manipulate the data. The currentCacheValue is trimed to delimite
	//the heading and tailing junk spaces.
  spConsumer.manipulateData( pathHolder.getPath( ), this.currentCacheValue.trim() );
		this.currentCacheValue = "";

Thanks.
Lin

