Sorry, my report was a bit to short. So next try:
The reason why we report this bug is that we want to generate code from the AST, so we we have a strong need that everything in the AST is correct. The following example is out of "The C++ Standard" (p. 250, Bjarne Stroustrup, ISBN 0-470-84674-7), because the static example is missing in "1997 C++ Public Review Document".

The "template" keyword is referenced to the "qualified-id"-node in the standard. There's no such item in the AST. We currently think the simplest thing is to put this information in ICPPASTQualifiedName.

#ifndef X_H_
#define X_H_

class X
{
public:
	X();
	virtual ~X();
	template<int> X* alloc();
	template<int> static X* adjust();
};

template<class T> void f(T* p)
{
	//T* p1 = p->alloc<100>();
	T* p1 = p->template alloc<100>();
	T::template adjust<100>();
}

#endif /*X_H_*/

